<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="46" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1424,2030]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Chen, 1964" authorityName="Wu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1964" box="[151,740,1424,1450]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globosa" subGenus="Scolelepis">
<emphasis box="[151,270,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[287,406,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[424,517,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">globosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[524,740,1424,1450]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Wu, B. L. &amp; Chen, M. (1964) A new species of polychaete worm of the Family Spionidae from Chushan Archipelago, East China Sea. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 1 (1), 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1964">
Wu &amp; Chen, 
<number box="[681,740,1424,1450]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as 
<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Chen, 1964" authorityName="Wu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1964" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globosa" subGenus="Nerinides">
<emphasis box="[1075,1194,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[1212,1326,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Nerinides</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,1424,1449]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">globosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[151,371,1462,1488]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Wu, B. L. &amp; Chen, M. (1964) A new species of polychaete worm of the Family Spionidae from Chushan Archipelago, East China Sea. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 1 (1), 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1964">
Wu &amp; Chen, 
<number box="[309,371,1462,1488]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on material from the intertidal flat around Zhoushan archipelago in the East 
<collectingCountry box="[1366,1436,1462,1488]" name="China" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">China</collectingCountry>
Sea. After that, there were no additional reports of the species. According to the original description, the species is characterized by globular expansions at the bases of the palps. It also can be clearly separated from other Chinese 
<taxonomicName box="[326,448,1579,1604]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[326,448,1579,1604]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the combination of the characters of the presence of tridentate hooded hooks and occipital tentacle. Therefore, we consider it to be a valid species, but unfortunately neither the 
<typeStatus box="[1385,1436,1617,1643]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">type</typeStatus>
materials nor other representative samples are available for examination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1424,2030]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
Although the validity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Chen, 1964" authorityName="Wu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1964" box="[503,1120,1694,1720]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globosa" subGenus="Scolelepis">
<emphasis box="[503,628,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[647,771,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[790,887,1695,1720]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">globosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[895,1120,1694,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Wu, B. L. &amp; Chen, M. (1964) A new species of polychaete worm of the Family Spionidae from Chushan Archipelago, East China Sea. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 1 (1), 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1964">
Wu &amp; Chen, 
<number box="[1059,1120,1694,1720]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is certain, the subgeneric arrangement of the species is confusing. 
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[649,884,1733,1759]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Wu, B. L. &amp; Chen, M. (1964) A new species of polychaete worm of the Family Spionidae from Chushan Archipelago, East China Sea. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 1 (1), 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1964">
Wu &amp; Chen (
<number box="[812,875,1733,1759]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
placed the species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[1319,1436,1733,1758]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Nerinides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1319,1436,1733,1758]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Nerinides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any detailed explanation. The original description of the species lacks the morphological characters of the neuropodial postsetal lamellae in the posterior part of body, which is the most important taxonomic character for the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[466,580,1849,1874]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Nerinides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[466,580,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Nerinides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Pettibone" box="[740,940,1849,1875]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Pettibone, M. H. (1963) Revision of some genera of polychaete worms of the family Spionidae, including the description of a new species of Scolelepis. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 76, 89 - 104." type="journal article" year="1963">
Pettibone (
<number box="[867,931,1849,1875]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1963.0">1963</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Detailed information on the shapes of the neuropodial postsetal lamellae in this species is obviously needed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1424,2030]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,152,216]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">
The concept of the division of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[683,802,1927,1952]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[683,802,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
into the subgenera 
<taxonomicName box="[1036,1155,1927,1952]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1036,1155,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Scolelepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1214,1389,1927,1952]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Parascolelepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1389,1927,1952]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="46">Parascolelepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been followed by various subsequent authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Imajima" box="[783,956,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Imajima, M. (1992) Spionidae (Annelida, Polychaeta) from Japan VIII. The genus Scolelepis. Bulletin of the National Science Museum, Tokyo, Series A (Zoology), 18 (1), 1 - 34." type="journal article" year="1992">
Imajima 
<number box="[892,956,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake" box="[970,1113,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Blake, J. A. (1996) Family Spionidae Grube, 1850. In: Blake, J. A., Hilbig, B. &amp; Scott, P. H. (Eds.), Taxonomic Atlas of the Benthic Fauna of the Santa Maria Basin and Western Santa Barbara Channel. The Annelida. Part 3 Polychaeta: Orbiniidae to Cossuridae. Santa Barbara Museum of Natural History, Vol. 6, Santa Barbara, California, pp. 81 - 224." type="journal article" year="1996">
Blake 
<number box="[1049,1113,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="1996.0">1996</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Delgado-Blas" box="[1127,1368,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" refString="Delgado-Blas, V. H. (2006) Partial revision of Scolelepis (Polychaeta: Spionidae) from the Grand Caribbean Region, with the description of two new species and a key to species recorded in the area. Contributions to Zoology, 75 (1 / 2), 75 - 97." type="journal article" year="2006">
Delgado-Blas 
<number box="[1302,1368,1965,1991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="46" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The former is characterized by having uni-, bi- or tridentate hooded hooks, while the latter has multidentate hooded hooks. In order to avoid confusion, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Chen, 1964" authorityName="Wu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1964" box="[666,1250,152,178]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globosa" subGenus="Nerinides">
<emphasis box="[666,785,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Scolelepis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[802,916,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Nerinides</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[934,1027,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">globosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[1034,1250,152,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" refString="Wu, B. L. &amp; Chen, M. (1964) A new species of polychaete worm of the Family Spionidae from Chushan Archipelago, East China Sea. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 1 (1), 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1964">
Wu &amp; Chen, 
<number box="[1191,1250,152,178]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
should be cited as 
<taxonomicName authority="Wu &amp; Chen, 1964" authorityName="Wu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="1964" box="[182,768,190,216]" class="Polychaeta" family="Spionidae" genus="Scolelepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spionida" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="globosa" subGenus="Scolelepis">
<emphasis box="[182,301,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Scolelepis</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[318,437,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">Scolelepis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[454,547,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="48">globosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wu" box="[554,768,190,216]" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" refString="Wu, B. L. &amp; Chen, M. (1964) A new species of polychaete worm of the Family Spionidae from Chushan Archipelago, East China Sea. Acta Zootaxonomica Sinica, 1 (1), 195 - 198." type="journal article" year="1964">
Wu &amp; Chen, 
<quantity box="[709,768,190,216]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.98856" pageId="11" pageNumber="48" unit="in" value="1964.0">1964</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in subsequent studies.
</paragraph>
